            <h3>Who is Euromancer?</h3>
            <p>Unlike Neuromancer, the artificial intelligence in William Gibson's 1984 novel of the same name,¬†`Euromancer`¬†is a living person with emotions, dreams, and biases. His long journey into cyberspace has given him a pan-European identity, yet it has also resulted in disillusionment. The EU he once fell in love with has shifted from integration and openness to exclusion and walls. Meanwhile, cyberspace has fallen into techno-feudalism ‚ÄĒ closed proprietary platforms backed by nation-states and oligarchs.
            <br>This is where his romance with "Post-Europe" begins.</p>
